(H, \langle\cdot,\cdot\rangle_H)
A:H\times H\rightarrow \mathbb{R}
{\bf A}\in\mathcal{L}(H)
{\bf S}_1
{\bf S}_2\in\mathcal{L}(H)
\alpha_1,\alpha_2 > 0
A(\sigma,\tau)\ =\ \langle{\bf A}(\sigma), \tau\rangle_H.
\langle {\bf S}^*_1{\bf A}(\tau), \tau\rangle_H\ \geq\ \alpha_1\|\tau\|_H^2\quad \mbox{ and }\quad \langle{\bf A}{\bf S}_2(\tau), \tau\rangle_H\ \geq\ \alpha_2\|\tau\|_H^2\quad \forall\ \tau\in H.
